  "text": "Definition of the quantum theory requires gauge-fixing. This is customarily accomplished by imposing Siegel gauge b 0 |Ψ = 0. One must introduce Fadeev-Popov ghosts for this gauge fixing, and in fact, since the gauge symmetry is reducible, one needs ghosts for ghosts, and ghosts for ghosts for ghosts, ad infinitum. It is a famous miracle [CITATION_1] that the full second-quantized gauge-fixed action + ghosts can be written in the form",
